In a #medium pot{}, bring 3 cups water and the @wheat berries{3/4%cup} to a boil with a
large pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, cover, and reduce to a simmer for ~{35-40%minutes},
until tender. Drain and rinse under cold water.

Meanwhile, poach the chicken: fill a #medium tall-sided pan{} with 2-inches water and bring
to a simmer. Season the water with @salt{}, then add the @chicken breasts{2} and simmer
for about ~{15%minutes}, flipping half way through until cooked through.

> Be sure not to let the water boil or the chicken will be tough instead of juicy!

While the chicken poaches, thinly slice the @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), keeping the green
and white parts separate. Mince the @tarragon{1%sprig}(minced). Zest and halve the
@lemon{1}(zested and halved). Thinly slice the @radishes{3}(thinly sliced).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, the scallion whites, lemon zest,
tarragon, and a generous squeeze of lemon. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the chicken is cooked through, let it cool slightly, then cut into ½-inch cubes.
Toss with the mayonnaise mixture, radishes, @dried cherries{1%ounce}, and wheat
berries. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> You can use the pot you cooked the wheat berries in to save yourself a dish!

Toss the @arugula{4%ounce} with @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon, and a
pinch of salt and pepper.

Serve the chicken salad on top of a bed of arugula, then sprinkle with the
@sliced almonds{1%ounce} and scallion greens. Enjoy!